<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-624-876  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 624 876.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  June 25 1990 v4 n25 p4(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>GSA inches toward micro schedule finish. (US General ServicesAdministration adds firms to its microcomputer schedule contractsprior to Jun 30, 90 deadline)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Danca, Richard A.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The US General Services Administration (GSA) continues to addcompanies to or renew microcomputer schedule contracts prior tothe Jun 30, 1990 deadline, but many firms have yet to receive newschedules for the forthcoming year.andP;  These include over 80companies that participated last year and whose contracts havebeen extended to June.andP;  Eight of the ten largest sellers last yearhave not received contracts, though 239 schedules have beenawarded by early June.andP;  The delays in many cases are a result ofthe inability of GSA to get adequate pricing information orcurrent schedule holders are offering products at higher pricesthan GSA wants to pay.andP;  The GSA has added laptop and portablecomputers to the existing categories, which include desktopcomputers, monitors, modems, other peripherals, and software.andO;Many firms have complained about the GSA's requests for pricinginformation.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Product AcquisitionPurchasing SystemsMicrocomputersGovernment ContractsRequirements AnalysisUnited States. General Services Administration.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>